\i \cf0 Directions
\i0 \
Pour the juice in a medium sized saucepan and place it over medium heat. Add the rosemary to the juice and let it simmer till the juice is reduced to less than half of its consistency. Remember that this is what would determine the intensity of the flavors of the juice. Now add in the honey, garlic and let it simmer and mix well with the juice. Remove the garlic and add the herb salt and vinegar. \
\
In a separate saucepan heat water and add corn starch to it to make a thick paste. Add this into your red pomegranate sauce to allow it to thicken. \
